#
# Source-direct completion: every subcommand alias + every flag below is
# verbatim from core/entry.go `Execute()` urfave/cli App definition and the
# README.md "Function Command Description" section on the DataMiner tip.
#
# Direct deps from go.mod:
#   github.com/dlclark/regexp2 v1.10.0   ← canonical Go Perl/.NET-compatible
#                                          regex (this axis) — by Doug Clark
#                                          (dlclark) — supports lookarounds,
#                                          atomic groups, conditionals
#                                          (features stdlib `regexp` lacks)
#   github.com/urfave/cli                (CLI framework)
#   golang.org/x/net/proxy               (SOCKS5 proxy support)
#
# DataMiner uses dlclark/regexp2 for the `-p, --pattern` flag in the
# SearchSensitiveData (SS) module, allowing arbitrary Perl-flavor regex
# (including lookarounds) to scan database content for sensitive fields.
# Stdlib `regexp` would be insufficient because it lacks lookarounds and
# atomic groups required by many DLP-style patterns.
#
# === AXIS 165 CONTINUES — PCRE2 / Perl-flavor regex ecosystem ===
# Axis position: Go=220 continues Axis 165 (slot 2/0/0).  Canonical Go
# Perl-compatible regex library is `dlclark/regexp2` by Doug Clark — a
# pure-Go port of the .NET regex engine providing the full Perl-flavor
# feature set.  Used by dop251/goja (6,891★ pure-Go ECMAScript engine for
# RegExp.prototype semantics), DataMiner DLP scanning, evanw/esbuild's
# wasm-side string operations (indirect), and any Go tool needing
# lookarounds or atomic groups.
#
# Cycle position in current 3+1 micro-cycle:
#   Rust=220   _dosr / _chsr        ← previous round (axis 165 OPENS at 1/0/0)
#   Go=220     ← THIS FILE          (axis 165 continues, slot 2/0/0)
#   TS-Node=220 ← next round        (axis 165 CLOSES at triple-220, slot 1/1/1)
